This paper deals with the problem of classifying structural variability in noisy projections of biological macromolecules using Cryo-EM. The proposed method involves estimating the covariance matrix of the 3D structure present in the molecules being imaged, which is a problem that falls under the purview of computer vision (cs.CV) and machine learning (cs.LG, cs.AI). The method also involves optimization using conjugate gradient, which is a numerical analysis technique that falls under the purview of computer graphics (cs.GR) and numerical analysis (cs.NA). Therefore, the most likely arXiv CS sub-categories for this paper are cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.GR, and cs.NA.
